CSS Grid is a powerful layout system that lets you create two-dimensional layouts â€” with rows and columns.
Makes complex layouts easier and cleaner
Gives full control over spacing, alignment, and structure
Responsive and flexible

Example:
.container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; /* 3 equal columns */
  gap: 10px;
}

<div class="container">
  <div>1</div>
  <div>2</div>
  <div>3</div>
</div>
Properties:
Property	Use
display: grid	(Enables grid layout)
grid-template-columns	Defines number/size of columns
grid-template-rows	Defines rows
gap	(Sets space between rows/columns)
grid-column / grid-row	Positioning items inside the grid


CSS Grid is used to build layouts using rows and columns, offering more control than Flexbox for complex designs.

